uttled at Along Bay, French Indochina.<ref name=\"French Navy in WWII\">{{cite book |url= https://books.google.com/?id=DKuqDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA361&lpg=PA361&dq=vessel,+Capitaine+Coulon#v=onepage&q=vessel%2C%20Capitaine%20Coulon&f=false |title=French Navy in WWII  |publisher=Googlebooks.com |accessdate=13 April 2017|isbn=9781682470602 |date=15 July 2016 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Kaiko Maru||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The auxiliary [[gunboat]] was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Pacific Ocean]] south of [[Honshu]] by {{USS|Trepang|SS-412|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=seekrieg194503/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|French hydrographic vessel|La Perouse||2}} \n|flag={{navy|France}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[Survey ship|hydrographic vessel]] was scuttled at Vinh Long, French Indochina.<ref name=\"French Navy in WWII\">{{cite book |url= https://books.google.com/?id=DKuqDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA361&lpg=PA361&dq=vessel,+Capitaine+Coulon#v=onepage&q=vessel%2C%20Capitaine%20Coulon&f=false |title=French Navy in WWII  |publisher=Googlebooks.com |accessdate=13 April 2017|isbn=9781682470602 |date=15 July 2016 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|M-412||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Granville Raid]]: The [[M-class minesweeper (Germany)|M 1940-class minesweeper]] ran aground at [[Granville, Manche|Granville]], France, and was scuttled.<ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=6113653|shipname=M-412 |accessdate=4 August 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|French patrol vessel|Maurice Long||2}} \n|flag={{navy|France}}\n|desc=World War II: The patrol vessel was scuttled in the Mekong River at [[C\u1ea7n Th\u01a1|Can Tho]], French Indochina.<ref name=\"French Navy in WWII\">{{cite book |url= https://books.google.com/?id=DKuqDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA361&lpg=PA361&dq=vessel,+Capitaine+Coulon#v=onepage&q=vessel%2C%20Capitaine%20Coulon&f=false |title=French Navy in WWII  |publisher=Googlebooks