edom/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[European Alliance of Peoples and Nations|EAPN]]\n|{{Composition bar 2|3|13|hex={{European Conservatives and Reformists/meta/color}}}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2014|June|04}}\n|-\n|{{FIN}}\n|[[Finns Party]]\n''Perussuomalaiset (PS)''<br />\n|style=\"background:{{Movement for a Europe of Nations and Freedom/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[European Alliance of Peoples and Nations|EAPN]]\n|{{Composition bar 2|2|13|hex={{European Conservatives and Reformists/meta/color}}}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2014|June|04}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | {{flag|Germany}}\n|[[Liberal Conservative Reformers]]|{{efn|[[Bernd Lucke]] left [[Alternative for Germany|AfD]] with 4 more MEPs after losing leadership of his party in 2015. The remaining two AfD members, [[Beatrix von Storch]] and [[Marcus Pretzell]] were expelled from the ECR group in 2016.|name=|group=}}<br>''Liberal-Konservative Reformer'' ''(LKR)''\n|style=\"background:{{Alliance of Conservatives and Reformists in Europe/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Alliance of Conservatives and Reformists in Europe|ACRE]]\n|{{Composition bar 2|4|96|hex={{European Conservatives and Reformists/meta/color}}}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2014|June|12}}\n|-\n|C Alliance<br>''B\u00fcndnis C'' ''(AUF & PBC)''\n|style=\"background:{{European Christian Political Movement/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[European Christian Political Movement|ECPM]]\n|{{Composition bar 2|1|96|hex={{European Conservatives and Reformists/meta/color}}}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2014|June|04}}\n|-\n|Independent{{efn|Left [[Liberal Conservative Reformers|LKR]].|name=|group=}}\n|style=\"background:{{Independent/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Independent politician|Independent]]\n|{{Composition bar 2|1|96|hex={{European Conservatives and Reformists/meta/color}}}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2018|September|29}}\n|-\n|{{flag|Greece}}\n| Independent{{efn|[[Notis Marias]] left [[Independent Greeks|ANEL]].}}\n|style=\"background:{{Independent/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Independent politician|Independent]]\n|{{Composition bar 2|1|21|hex={{European Conservatives and Reformists/meta/color}}}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2014|June|04}}\n|-\n|{{IRL}}\n|[[Fianna F\u00e1il]]{{efn|Brian Crowley was the sole member of [[Fianna F\u00e1il]] elected in the 2014 election; following his announcement that he was joining the ECR, Fianna F\u00e1il withdrew the party whip. Crowley remains a member of the [[Fianna F\u00e1il]] party as a whole, but has been excluded from its cross-Parliamentary caucus.|name=|group=}}<br>''Fianna F\u00e1il \u2013 An P\u00e1irt\u00ed Poblacht\u00e1nach'' ''(FF)''<br />\n|style=\"background:{{Non-Inscrits/meta/color}}\" |\n|''None''\n|{{Composition bar 2|1|11|hex={{European Conservatives and Reformists/meta/color}}}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2014|June|23}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{flag|Italy}}\n|[[Brothers of Italy]]<br>''Fratelli d'Italia'' ''(FdI)''\n| style=\"background:{{Alliance of Conservatives and Reformists in Europe/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Alliance of Conservatives and Reformists in Europe|ACRE]]\n|{{Composition bar 2|2|73|hex={{European Conservatives and Reformists/meta/color}}}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2018|December|17}}\n|-\n|[[Direction Italy]]<br>''Direzione Italia'' ''(DI)''\n|style=\"background:{{Alliance of Conservatives and Reformists in Europe/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Alliance of Conservatives and Reformists in Europe|ACRE]]\n|{{Composition bar 2|2|73|hex={{European Conservatives and Reformists/meta/color}}}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2015|May|19}}\n|-\n| {{flag|Latvia}}\n| [[National Alliance (Latvia)|National Alliance]]<br>''Nacion\u0101l\u0101 Apvien\u012bba'' ''(NA)''\n|style=\"background:{{Alliance of Conservatives and Reformists in Europe/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Alliance of Conservatives and Reformists in Europe|ACRE]]\n| {{Composition bar 2|1|8|hex={{European Conservatives and Reformists/meta/color}}}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2009|June|22}}\n|-\n| {{flag|Lithuania}}\n| [[Electoral Action of Poles in Lithuania \u2013 Christian Families Alliance|Electoral Action of Poles in Lithuania]]{{efn|Full name: Electoral A