e Sportive du Sahel V.C.|\u00c9toile Sportive du Sahel]]<br> {{flagicon|TUN}} [[CS Sfaxien (volleyball)|CS Sfaxien]]<br> {{flagicon|KSA}} Al-Ettifaq<br> {{flagicon|KSA}} Al-Nassr<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[BBTS Bielsko-Bia\u0142a]]\n}}\n\n'''Arie Cornelis Brokking'''  is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[volleyball]] coach, a head coach of [[Poland|Polish]] club [[BBTS Bielsko-Bia\u0142a]].\n\n==Career as coach==\nIn 2007 Brokking was appointed under [[UK Government]] funding to lead the Great Britain men's volleyball team into the [[2012 Summer Olympics]]. At the [[2012 Summer Olympics]], they lost all 5 matches. Due to the team financial problems, Brokking left the GB team to become a coach in [[Tunisia]].<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/olympics/19258127 ''Harry Brokking leaves role as Great Britain volleyball coach''] \u2013 bbc.com \u2013 14.08.2012</ref>\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n* '''[[CEV Champions League]]'''\n** [[File:Bronze medal europe.svg|16px]] 1997/1998 \u2013 [[Paris Volley]]\n\n* '''[[African Clubs Championship (volleyball)|CAVB African Club Championship]]'''\n** [[File:Bronze medal africa.svg|16px]] Tunisia 2015 \u2013 [[\u00c9toile Sportive du Sahel V.C.|\u00c9toile Sportive du Sahel]]\n\n* '''National championships'''\n** '''1992/1993''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] German Championship, with USC M\u00fcnster\n** '''1994/1995''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Pro A (volleyball)|French Championship]], with [[Paris Volley]]\n** '''1995/1996''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Pro A (volleyball)|French Championship]], with [[Paris Volley]]\n** '''1996/1997''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] French Cup, with [[Paris Volley]]\n** '''1996/1997''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Pro A (volleyball)|French Championship]], with [[Paris Volley]]\n** '''1997/1998''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Pro A (volleyball)|French Championship]], with [[Paris Volley]]\n** '''1999/2000''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Pro A (volleyball)|French Championship]], with [[Tourcoing Lille M\u00e9tropole Volley-Ball|Tourcoing LM]]\n** '''2000/2001''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Pro A (volleyball)|French Championship]], with [[Tourcoing Lille M\u00e9tropole Volley-Ball|Tourcoing LM]]\n** '''2001/2002''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Pro A (volleyball)|French Championship]], with [[Tourcoing Lille M\u00e9tropole Volley-Ball|Tourcoing LM]]\n** '''2012/2013''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Tunisian Men's Volleyball League|Tunisian Championship]], with [[\u00c9toile Sportive du Sahel V.C.|\u00c9toile Sportive du Sahel]]\n** '''2013/2014''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Tunisian Men's Volleyball League|Tunisian Championship]], with [[\u00c9toile Sportive du Sahel V.C.|\u00c9toile Sportive du Sahel]]\n** '''2014/2015''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Tunisian Men's Volleyball League|Tunisian Championship]], with [[\u00c9toile Sportive du Sahel V.C.|\u00c9toile Sportive du Sahel]]\n** '''2015/2016''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Tunisian Men's Volleyball League|Tunisian Championship]], with [[CS Sfaxien (volleyball)|CS Sfaxien]]\n** '''2018/2019''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] Saudian Championship, with Al-Nassr\n\n* '''National teams'''\n** '''1989''' [[File:Bronze medal europe.svg|16px]] [[1989 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]], with [[Netherlands men's national volleyball team|Netherlands]] \n** '''1990''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[1990 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]], with [[Netherlands men's national volleyball team|Netherlands]] \n** '''1991''' [[File:Bronze medal europe.svg|16px]] [[1991 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]], with [[Netherlands men's national volleyball team|Netherlands]] \n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://archive.is/20130122003318/http://www.elteevolley.com/tpc/